name: entry-list

mkey.description: The external resource name to query.

status_only.description: Set to true to retrieve resource file status only. (Skip valid/invalid entries.)

include_notes.description: Set to true to retrieve notes on the resource file.

counts_only.description: Set to true to retrive valid/invalid counts only. (Skip entries.)

GET.summary:
Retrieve resource file status with a list of valid/invalid entries for the specific external resource. Empty lines and comment lines are not returned.
Access Group: sysgrp.cfg

help: Retrieve resource file status with a list of valid/invalid entries for the specific external resource. Empty lines and comment lines are not returned.

status.title: Connection Status
status.description: Connection status to the external resource.

error.title: Error Message
error.description: Error message for when the external resource entries cannot be retrieved.

error_code.title: Error Code
error_code.description: Error code for when the external resource entries cannot be retrieved.

http_status_code.name: http_status_code
http_status_code.title: HTTP Connection Status Code

conn_attempt_time.title: Connection Attempt Timestamp

resource_file_status.title: File Status

last_content_update_time.name: last_content_update_time
last_content_update_time.title: Last Content Update Timestamp
last_content_update_time.description: Timestamp of when the external resource file was last updated.

last_conn_success_time.name: last_conn_success_time
last_conn_success_time.title: Last Successful Connection Timestamp
last_conn_success_time.description: Timestamp of the last successful connection to the external resource.

accepted_count.name: accepted_count

overflow.title: Overflow of Entries

matched_valid.name: matched_valid
